What this does (with clean segments now)

For each token row in the list:

Get its pei_token value (lowercase per ADR-039 sister discovery — the OData logical name)
trim(...) defensively trims whitespace (in case admin entered BU-Engineering with stray spaces in a seed token)
contains(segments_array, trimmed_token) — checks exact array membership because the first arg is an array (not a string)
This is the segment-equality match per ADR-038


Filter keeps only token rows whose pei_token matches at least one segment exactly

Output: an array of token rows that matched. Length 0/1/2+ drives the next step.
